Interface TransactionRegisteredEvent<K,V>

All Superinterfaces:
Event<K,V>, TransactionalEvent<K,V>
All Known Implementing Classes:
EventImpl
public interface TransactionRegisteredEvent<K,V> extends TransactionalEvent<K,V>
This event is passed in to any method annotated with TransactionRegistered. Note that this event is only delivered after the fact, i.e., you will never see an instance of this event with Event.isPre() being set to true.
